The paper deals with image-to-image translation problems, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of adversarial networks is a popular technique in both of these fields. The paper also discusses the use of conditional networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper's focus on loss functions and their automatic learning could also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
